| Maximum Sharpe | | | | |
| Risk Parity | | | | |

---

## Efficient Frontier

The dashboard generates simulated portfolios and visualizes:

- Return
- Volatility
- Portfolio efficiency

---

## Portfolio Growth

Displays cumulative wealth evolution over time.

---

## Drawdown Analysis

Shows portfolio losses and recovery periods.

---

## Portfolio Allocation

Visualizes the asset weights of the Maximum Sharpe portfolio.

---

# Results

Based on the backtest:

| Portfolio | Annual Return | Sharpe Ratio | Maximum Drawdown |
|---|---:|---:|---:|
| Maximum Sharpe | 36.0% | 1.42 | -35.8% |
| Equal Weight | 20.1% | 1.02 | -32.9% |
| Risk Parity | 17.8% | 0.96 | -31.8% |
| Minimum Variance | 13.1% | 0.80 | -26.4% |

---

# Interpretation

The Maximum Sharpe portfolio produced the strongest risk-adjusted performance.

Key observations:

- Maximum Sharpe achieved the highest return and Sharpe ratio.
- Minimum Variance provided the lowest volatility and best downside protection.
- Risk Parity produced a balanced risk allocation.
- Equal Weight remained a competitive benchmark.

The results demonstrate the trade-off between return optimization and risk management.

